  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he saw also a certain poor widow,.... Whom he took particular notice of above all the rest: the poor, and the widow, are regarded by him, and are his care; nor are their mean services, done in faith, and from a principle of love, despised by him, but preferred to the greater services of others, where faith and love are wanting: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "casting in thither two mites; the value of a farthing. The Persic version renders it, \"two bottoms of yarn\"; See Gill on Mark 12:42, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "casting in thither two mites; the value of a farthing. The Persic version renders it, \"two bottoms of yarn\"; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
